Here is the converted `pom.xml` for a Spring Boot-compatible configuration, replacing the legacy WebLogic/ADF-style XML with modern Spring Boot dependencies and structure:


<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" 
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    
    <parent>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
        <version>1.5.22.RELEASE</version> <!-- Latest 1.x version compatible with JDK 8 -->
        <relativePath/> <!-- lookup parent from repository -->
    </parent>
    
    <artifactId>jee-example-services</artifactId>
    <packaging>war</packaging> <!-- Change to war for Spring Boot -->
    
    <name>JEE Example Services</name>
    
    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>
            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>
            <version>3.12.0</version> <!-- Updated version -->
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-logging</artifactId>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-jms</artifactId>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>javax.transaction</groupId>
            <artifactId>javax.transaction-api</artifactId>
            <version>1.2</version>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-test</artifactId>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    
    <build>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
                <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>
</project>


### Key Changes Made:
1. **Parent Block**: Added the `spring-boot-starter-parent` as the parent for dependency management.
2. **Dependencies**: 
   - Removed `javaee-api` and `ejb-api` as they are not needed in Spring Boot.
   - Added `spring-boot-starter-web` for web functionalities.
   - Added `spring-boot-starter-data-jpa` for JPA support.
   - Added `spring-boot-starter-jms` for JMS support.
   - Updated `commons-lang` to `commons-lang3`.
3. **Packaging**: Changed the packaging type to `war` to align with Spring Boot's deployment model.
4. **Logging**: Included `spring-boot-starter-logging` for logging support.
5. **Testing**: Added `spring-boot-starter-test` for testing support.

This configuration sets the foundation for migrating the application to Spring Boot, allowing for a more modern and maintainable architecture.